paedophiles were operating in the northern Brisbane suburbs and the Gold Coast in the early 1970s.</p><p>Jan Doyle, a senior social worker for the Queensland Department of Children's Services in the 1970s, told the royal commission into institutional responses to child sexual abuse the number of runaways was exceptional in 1973.</p><p>She also said that in 1975 she was deeply concerned about the whereabouts of one boy, HT, who frequently ran away from Alkira, so she spoke to the police Juvenile Aid Bureau which expressed concern about the paedophile ring and boys being taken to Sydney.</p><p>Doyle said she sought permission to run an advertisement with a photograph of HT requesting information about his whereabouts and that she remembered talking to welfare departments in New South Wales and Victoria about him.</p><p>Simeon Beckett, counsel advising the commission, asked her if any additional resources were allocated by the department to the Salvation Army home to ensure boys were protected from the prostitution racket.</p><p>\"Not that I am aware of,\" Doyle said.</p><p>But in 1973 the number of times children absconded was unusually high, she told the royal commission hearing in Sydney on Thursday.</p><p>Her evidence follows that of Salvation Army whistleblower retired major Clifford Randall, who told the hearing on Tuesday that in 1975 particularly the home was in a situation where boys were disappearing for more than a few days.</p><p>Former Queensland assistant police commissioner David Jefferies – who was with the Juvenile Aid Bureau in the 1970s – on Wednesday told the hearing it had received information that a Queensland millionaire, known as JA, was flying boys to Sydney to be abused as part of a paedophile ring.</p><p>\"This JA was certainly known as a millionaire and had, I believe, a construction business, and we certainly had received information about children actually going to his home,\" Jefferies said.</p><p>\"We were aware that boys in state care and from some institutions had in fact been flown to Sydney.\"</p><p>The hearing continues.</p>","headline":"Spate of runaways from boys'  home as police pursued paedophile ring: inquiry","trailText":"Social worker says she concerned about one boy in 1975 who frequently ran away from the Salvation Army home Alkira","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"theguardian.com","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3mgxn","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/6/1391661708174/e7570ba6-2acd-49e4-841f-2c5ea829e000-140x84.jpeg","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/6/1391661708174/e7570ba6-2acd-49e4-841f-2c5ea829e000-140x84.jpeg","wordcount":"418","commentable":"false","internalContentCode":"429029182","allowUgc":"false","internalComposerCode":"52f30ef0e4b0530e249db040","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Australian Associated Press","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-02-06T00:00:00Z","internalPageCode":"2039063","productionOffice":"AUS","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-02-09T04:52:37Z"},"rights":{"syndicatable":false,"subscriptionDatabases":false},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/feb/06/spate-runaways-police-pursued-paedophile-ring","apiUrl":"http://internal.content.guardianapis.com/world/2014/feb/06/spate-runaways-police-pursued-paedophile-ring","tags":[{"id":"world/royal-commission-into-institutional-responses-to-child-sexual-abuse","webTitle":"Royal commission into institutional responses to child sexual abuse","type":"keyword","sectionId":"world","sectionName":"World news","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/world/royal-commission-into-institutional-responses-to-child-sexual-abuse","apiUrl":"http://internal.content.guardianapis.com/world/royal-commission-into-institutional-responses-to-child-sexual-abuse","references":[]},{"id":"world/australia","webTitle":"Australia","type":"keyword","sectionId":"world","sectionName":"World news",