ff.</p><p>Craig Kreeger, Virgin Atlantic chief executive, said: \"Despite the best efforts of our employees, external factors such as increasing costs and a weakening Australian dollar have affected our profitability.\"</p><p>\"These are still difficult times for the airline industry and as part of our strategy to operate more efficiently we need to deploy our aircraft to routes with the right level of demand to be financially viable.\"</p><p>Virgin Australia, in which Branson retains a minor stake, is a separate company and continues to operate as a domestic rival to Qantas in Australia, with codeshare agreements with Etihad and Singapore airlines for international flights.</p>","headline":"Virgin Atlantic drops flights to Australia","trailText":"<p>Airline to cease flights from Britain to Sydney in May, leaving BA as the only UK carrier to operate a direct service</p>","newspaperPageNumber":"26","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"The Guardian","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3mfmy","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/5/1391624006172/Virgin-Atlantic--006.jpg","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/5/1391624006172/Virgin-Atlantic--006.jpg","wordcount":"206","commentable":"false","internalContentCode":"429001590","allowUgc":"false","internalOctopusCode":"8649892","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Gwyn Topham, transport correspondent","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-02-06T00:00:00Z","internalPageCode":"2038899","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-02-08T18:15:57Z"},"rights":{"syndicatable":false,"subscriptionDatabases":false},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2014/feb/05/virgin-atlantic-australia-drops-flight-direct","apiUrl":"http://internal.content.guardianapis.com/business/2014/feb/05/virgin-atlantic-australia-drops-flight-direct","tags":[{"id":"business/virginatlantic","webTitle":"Virgin At